				{"name":"Dead Lover","short":"deadlo(1)","start":"2025-10-31 20:45","end":"2025-10-31 22:20","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Shot on 16mm, this delightfully strange love story follows a lonely gravedigger who tries to resurrect the love of her life. 
The blossoming love between a gravedigger (who smells like corpses) and a poet is cut short by a tragic accident. Grief-stricken and in possession of his severed finger, she uses her knowledge of dead bodies to try to bring him back in a highly inventive tale inspired by Frankenstein. Written by and starring Grace Glowicki and Ben Petrie (also in LIFF2025 film Honey Bunch).
Contains some bloody gore and references to death, grief and mental health. ","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/dead-lover-qz2t"},
				{"name":"Dreams","short":"dreams(2)","start":"2025-11-01 18:30","end":"2025-11-01 20:05","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Uncompromising Mexican director Michel Franco reunites with actress Jessica Chastain, whose cold precision powers an erotically charged political drama with a vicious sting in its tail. 
Chastain stars as rich philanthropist Jennifer opposite Isaac Hernández, who plays her lover, a young Mexican ballet dancer Fernando who dreams of international recognition and a life in the US. Believing she will support him, he leaves everything behind but his arrival disrupts her carefully curated world.

Contains themes of sexual violence.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/dreams-l6wg"},
				{"name":"Rental Family","short":"rental(1)","start":"2025-11-01 20:30","end":"2025-11-01 22:13","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Hikari’s Rental Family is a poignant comedy drama starring Oscar-winner Brendan Fraser as an American actor in Tokyo whose life is changed when he is cast for an unusual role. 
Philip (Fraser) has lived in Japan for seven years with little acting success until he’s recruited to play “sad American” at an actual funeral and is offered more stand-in roles working for a Japanese ‘rental family’ agency. As he immerses himself in his clients' worlds, he begins to form genuine bonds that blur the lines between performance and reality.
","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/rental-family-5y1n"},
				{"name":"The Black Hole","short":"blackh(1)","start":"2025-11-05 13:15","end":"2025-11-05 15:10","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Otherworldly creatures disrupt the lives of the residents of an apartment block in this delightful Estonian sci-fi triptych.
Aliens, giant spiders, and the malice of men unleash on a quiet neighbourhood when a black hole opens up nearby. Moonika Siimets explores the depths of humanity in this genre-bending deadpan sci-fi comedy, and manages to shine a light on the struggles of modern society - for women and the working class in particular - with humour, tenderness and a charming melancholy.

Contains scenes of domestic violence.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-black-hole-5lfn"},
				{"name":"The Virgin of the Quarry Lake","short":"virgin(1)","start":"2025-11-06 15:30","end":"2025-11-06 17:03","hls":"4 5","blurb":"A young girl’s first love awakens something darker within her when another woman gets in her way.
Diego has been teasing something of a romance with Natalia for a little while, but when he begins to see an older woman, Natalia refuses to sit back in silence. Quiet on the surface, much like its main character, The Virgin of the Quarry Lake is a captivating supernatural coming-of-age film that explores the depths of hormonal frustration, somewhere between The Virgin Suicides and The Craft.

Contains scenes of strong violence and sex.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-virgin-of-the-quarry-lake-1p1r"},
				{"name":"Dog of God","short":"dogofg(1)","start":"2025-11-08 12:30","end":"2025-11-08 14:02","hls":"4 5","blurb":"This surreal, graphic and beautifully twisted rotoscope animation explores witchcraft, werewolves and corruption in 17th-century Europe. 
When a small village consumed by religious fervour puts a woman on trial for witchcraft, the proceedings are disrupted by a stranger who claims to be a werewolf. As his influence spreads, fear turns to desire and the villagers descend into carnality and chaos. Inspired by folklore and real events, this striking, sexualised vision is unforgettable and unique.

Contains frequent animated nudity and depictions of sex. Brief sexual activity with an animal. Contains scenes of sexism. ","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/dog-of-god-1phr"},
				{"name":"The Holy Boy","short":"holybo(1)","start":"2025-11-08 14:45","end":"2025-11-08 16:47","hls":"2 4","blurb":"Something sinister lies beneath the picture-perfect aura of a small community in this Italian horror thriller.
Trying to run away from grief, a PE teacher takes a job in a gorgeous mountain village where everyone seems to get along. But it isn’t long before he uncovers the town’s strange rituals and their dire consequences on one particular teenager. The Holy Boy is a thought-provoking exploration of collective trauma and displaced grief from Paolo Strippoli.

Content scenes of graphic violence.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-holy-boy-fhzq"},
				{"name":"Ghost Elephants","short":"ghoste(2)","start":"2025-11-14 20:30","end":"2025-11-14 22:08","hls":"2 4 5","blurb":"Werner Herzog returns with Ghost Elephants, an enthralling journey into the misty Angolan highlands. 
Joining eccentric conservationist Dr Steve Boyes and master Namibian trackers, Herzog searches for a mythical herd of giant elephants, colossal creatures that exist between science and legend. With dazzling cinematography and Herzog’s singular narration, the film becomes a poetic meditation on obsession, vanishing cultures, and the enduring mysteries of nature.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/ghost-elephants-d2g9"},
				{"name":"A Useful Ghost","short":"ausefu(3)","start":"2025-11-15 20:15","end":"2025-11-15 22:25","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Visually striking, haunting and sharply funny, A Useful Ghost is a wildly inventive tale and unlike anything you’ll see this year. 
Director Ratchapoom Boonbunchachoke plays with form and tone in a bold and genre-defying debut that won the top prize at this year’s Cannes Critics’ Week. When Nat unexpectedly returns from the dead as a vacuum cleaner, she tries to reconnect with her husband, to the dismay of her in-laws. Beneath its surreal premise, the film explores Thai history, grief, and usefulness.

Contains scenes of nudity, violence, and death.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/a-useful-ghost-x8v6"},
				{"name":"Little Forest","short":"little1(2)","start":"2025-11-16 12:15","end":"2025-11-16 13:58","hls":"2 4 5","blurb":"With its sumptuous cooking sequences and tender reflections, Little Forest is a heartfelt ode to food, friendship, and the restorative pleasures of slowing down. 
In Yim Soon-rye’s gentle, nourishing drama, Hye-won (Kim Tae-ri - The Handmaiden) leaves behind the pressures of Seoul to return to her rural childhood home. As she tends the land, rekindles old friendships, and prepares seasonal meals of exquisite simplicity, she begins to heal from past wounds and rediscover her sense of self.
","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/little-forest-9lj5"}
			]
