				{"name":"Bugonia","short":"bugoni(1)","start":"2025-10-30 20:30","end":"2025-10-30 22:30","hls":"4","blurb":"The latest, much-anticipated collaboration between Yorgos Lanthimos and Emma Stone after Poor Things and Kinds of Kindness, Bugonia is a remake of cult Korean sci-fi comedy Save the Green Planet (2003). 
An obsessive conspiracy theorist (Jesse Plemons) and his cousin (Aidan Delbis) kidnap the high-powered CEO of a major pharma company (Emma Stone). They are convinced that she is part of an alien species involved in conducting experiments on humans and is intent on destroying Earth.
Contains flashing lights and imagery. ␀

Contains strong violence, injury detail, suicide, very strong language.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/bugonia-fh1q"},
				{"name":"A Private Life","short":"apriva(2)","start":"2025-11-03 13:00","end":"2025-11-03 14:43","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Jodie Foster shines in her first French-speaking lead role in Rebecca Zlotowski’s playful murder mystery.
Foster stars as Lilian Steiner, an American psychoanalyst in Paris whose life is upended after the sudden death of a long-standing patient. Convinced it was murder, Lilian throws herself into some amateur sleuthing, with her ex-husband (Daniel Auteuil) in tow. An elegant, unpredictable thriller laced with dark humour and Hitchcockian flair, A Private Life is a hugely entertaining delight.

Contains themes of suicide. ","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/a-private-life-z5k4"},
				{"name":"Alpha","short":"alpha(1)","start":"2025-11-03 15:15","end":"2025-11-03 17:23","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Julia Ducournau follows her award-winning Titane with this genre-bending family drama. 
Young Alpha returns home with a freshly branded tattoo made with a dirty needle, much to her mother’s panic. At the same time, her mysterious uncle returns and a virus spreads through the population, turning people into stone before crumbling to dust. A coming-of-age story cleverly blended with genre elements, Alpha is a more tender film from Ducournau, but one that’s as provocative as you’d expect.
Contains flashing lights and imagery. ␀

Contains scenes of drug use, graphic violence or injury, and homophobic attitudes and language.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/alpha-13cr"},
				{"name":"Omaha","short":"omaha(1)","start":"2025-11-04 16:15","end":"2025-11-04 17:38","hls":"2 4","blurb":"Two young siblings are taken on a mysterious cross-country journey in this performance-driven debut starring John Magaro (First Cow, Past Lives). 
Awoken by their dad and bustled into their car, Ella and Charlie discover an America they’ve never known. As their road trip unfolds, Ella grows suspicious of her father’s secrecy. Omaha embraces stripped-down intimacy, thriving on an incredible performance by Magaro, debuts from Molly Belle Wright and Wyatt Solis and a quietly impactful screenplay.

Contains upsetting scenes of child abandonment. ","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/omaha-skr2"},
				{"name":"The Mysterious Gaze of the Flamingo","short":"myster(1)","start":"2025-11-04 20:15","end":"2025-11-04 21:59","hls":"4","blurb":"An unknown disease spreads fear through a 1980s desert town, in this Cannes Un Certain Regard winner.
Teenage Lidia lives happily with her large queer family at Mama Boa’s cabaret, but their haven shatters when rumours spread that the illness transmits through two men by a simple glance of love. As accusations mount, Lidia must uncover the truth to protect them from the town. Part modern Western, part Almodóvar-inspired melodrama, Diego Céspedes’ striking debut marks a director to watch. 

Contains themes of homophobia and transphobia, scenes of domestic violence.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-mysterious-gaze-of-the-flamingo-yxrl"},
				{"name":"The Currents","short":"curren(1)","start":"2025-11-05 18:30","end":"2025-11-05 20:14","hls":"2 4","blurb":"A mesmerising psychological drama from acclaimed Argentine filmmaker Milagros Mumenthaler.
After accepting an award in Switzerland, fashion designer Lina impulsively jumps from a bridge into icy waters. On her return to Buenos Aires, something inside her has shifted, and she struggles to resume daily life with her husband and young daughter. Isabel Aimé González-Sola gives an outstanding performance as Lina in this singular and deeply resonant exploration of mental health, trauma and motherhood. 
","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-currents-r3s7"},
				{"name":"Follies","short":"follie(1)","start":"2025-11-06 10:45","end":"2025-11-06 12:26","hls":"4","blurb":"Eric K. Boulianne’s directorial debut, Follies, is a frank and funny exploration of modern love, sex, and intimacy.
After 16 years of marriage and two kids, François and Julie decide to open up their relationship, diving into swingers’ apps, awkward encounters, and new desires. Boulianne and co-star Catherine Chabot deliver a sharp, sex-positive comedy that balances farce with warmth, offering a witty, relatable reflection on the complexities of contemporary relationships.

Contains sexually explicit scenes.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/follies-9285"},
				{"name":"Sentimental Value","short":"sentim(1)","start":"2025-11-06 18:00","end":"2025-11-06 20:13","hls":"2 4","blurb":"After The Worst Person in the World, Renate Reinsve reunites with Joachim Trier in his latest Cannes-winning film, also starring Elle Fanning and Stellan Skarsgård.
Nora and Agnes confront old wounds when their director father, Gustav, returns to the family home to shoot a film based on their lives. With actress Nora refusing to take part, Gustav turns his attention to moulding a young American star (Fanning) into his daughter’s role. A masterfully skilled drama featuring Trier’s distinctive humour about grief and the healing power of art.

Contains themes and recreations of suicide.","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/sentimental-value-qhyt"},
				{
					"name":"Sirāt",
					"short":"sirt(3)",
					"start":"2025-11-07 20:15",
					"end":"2025-11-07 22:10",
					"hls":"4",
					"blurb":"Winner of the Cannes Jury Prize, Oliver Laxe’s Sirāt is a hallucinatory odyssey that demands to be experienced on the big screen.
A father (Sergi López) and his young son scour the Moroccan desert, searching for a daughter lost to the rave scene. Along the way, they join a nomadic community of ravers and are swept into a world of pounding techno, dust storms, and looming conflict. Shot on Super 16mm and with a thunderous score, this apocalyptic road trip is raw and unforgettable cinema.[Please note that there is now an additional screening of Sirāt on 31 October.]

Contains scenes with drug use and graphic violence.",
					"url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/sirat-t4bc"
				},
				{"name":"Calle Málaga","short":"callem(2)","start":"2025-11-12 18:00","end":"2025-11-12 19:56","hls":"4 5","blurb":"Director Maryam Touzani (Blue Caftan) returns with an endearing, big hearted drama boasting a towering performance from Carmen Maura. 
Maria Angeles is a 79-year-old Spanish woman who lives alone in Tangier, Morocco, and loves her hometown, the warm people and labyrinthine markets. However, her life is turned upside down when her daughter arrives from Madrid to sell the apartment where she’s always lived. Determined to stay, she digs in her heels and, unexpectedly, rediscovers love and sensuality.

","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/calle-malaga-529n"}
			]
		},
		{
			"name":"Everyman Cinema Screen 4",
			"events":[
				{
					"name":"The Blue Trail",
					"short":"bluetr(1)",
					"start":"2025-11-01 13:15",
					"end":"2025-11-01 14:40",
					"hls":"4 5",
					"blurb":"Gabriel Mascaro’s The Blue Trail is an entrancing, inspiring and visually lush film odyssey and a striking critique of ageism and authoritarianism.
In a near-future Brazil, the government gives priority to the country’s younger generations, while older people are put away in colonies so they will not “get in the way”. The 77-year-old Tereza (Denise Weinberg) refuses to submit and decides to escape, embarking on a transformative journey through the Amazon to fulfil one last wish before she loses her freedom.
[Please note that there is now an additional screening of␀ The Blue Trail on 4 November.] ␀

Contains scenes of graphic violence or injury, and nudity.",
					"url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/the-blue-trail-nj9f"
				},
				{"name":"In Symbiosis","short":"insymb(1)","start":"2025-11-01 15:15","end":"2025-11-01 17:18","hls":"2 4 5","blurb":"A vital and informative new documentary which sets out to create a deeper understanding of the current state of our food system. 
In Symbiosis systematically tracks how food is produced and distributed and is full of eye opening testimony from perceptive scientists, writers and activists. The film reveals how globalised industrial farming accelerates environmental degradation in response to consumer demand. It also reveals a drive for change and shows a path to sustainability and resilience.
","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/in-symbiosis-8kbs"},
				{"name":"Iracema (New 4K Restoration)","short":"iracem(2)","start":"2025-11-02 11:00","end":"2025-11-02 12:31","hls":"2 4 5","blurb":"Iracema is an atmospheric Brazilian road movie and a savage critique of the political hypocrisies of its time. 
It’s shot in guerilla style in a national security zone soon after the construction of the environmentally ruinous Trans-Amazonian Highway. Indigenous teenager Iracema leaves her family and falls into work as a prostitute. She meets Tião Brasil Grande, an unscrupulous truck driver and apologist for the Brazilian economic miracle, an unfortunate companion for a heartrending odyssey.
","url":"https://www.leedsfilm.com/whats-on/iracema-new-4k-restoration-1wzr"},
				{"name":"World Animation Competition 1","short":"worlda(2)","start":"2025-11-09 11:30","end":"2025-11-09 13:00","hls":"4 5","blurb":"We love animation at LIFF and we have a whole competition dedicated to short animated wonders. This first programme includes animations from Poland, Portugal, Egypt, Germany, Finland, Ecuador, Palestine, Switzerland, Estonia, Bulgaria, and Ireland.
␀
A mother and daughter connect over a Zoom call, where intergenerational perceptions of technology bring family conflicts and age-old bonds to light. With their thinking reflected on screens, can a digital space transform distance into a new kind of intimacy?England Premiere | Anastazja Naumenko | Poland | 2025 | 15 mins | Russian
Welcome to the dreamy nighttime world of apes. Unable to sleep, a man explores the hidden depths of his apartment block. With hints of comedy and the absurd, here lies a surreal landscape where those seeking connection escape from an ever-isolating reality.UK Premiere | Alexandre Sousa | Portugal, Hungary | 2025 | 12 mins | English
Through recalling personal memories of his childhood, a man explores his connection to his hair and how it has shaped his close relationships and wider life experience. Amusing and endearing in equal measure with a simple and effective visual style.Yorkshire Premiere | Sameh Alaa | France, Egypt | 2025 | 10 mins | Arabic
How do we warm ourselves up in cold times? One man ashamedly thinks a microwavable Hawaiian toastie is the answer. Detlev probes us to consider how we find solace in familiar routines. But what if that sought comfort was just on the other side of the glass?Yorkshire Premiere | Ferdinand Ehrhardt | Germany | 2024 | 13 mins | English
Weight-lifters, lovers, and fish dinners all vie for space in an apartment block. Dollhouse Elephant examines the tensions that arise when we attempt to live authentically. How we share space and adapt to ways of living are key themes in this vibrant short.England Premiere | Jenny J... [truncated]","url":""},
